## Applying This to OpenMRS on AWS

Thinking through what these roles would look like in a realistic small-to-medium OpenMRS deployment:

| Role | Who Might Fill It | Key Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| CISO / Security Lead | IT Director or Senior IT Staff | Sets encryption policy, leads incident response, aligns security with organizational goals |
| Risk Manager | IT Security Staff or GRC Analyst | Maintains risk register, conducts risk assessments, tracks mitigation progress |
| Compliance Officer | Operations Manager or dedicated staff | Manages HIPAA documentation, conducts staff training, handles audit preparation |
| System Owner | IT Manager or OpenMRS Administrator | Configures and maintains OpenMRS securely, manages access controls and patching |
| Authorizing Official | Medical Director or Executive Director | Reviews risk findings and formally authorizes the system to operate |

In a small clinic these five responsibilities might be covered by two or three people. That is realistic and not inherently a problem — as long as every responsibility is actually owned and not falling through the cracks.

